element.name: I Never Heard of Surgalstown by Orangetigerprawn, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

long-description.center: Well, at least not until today, so here it is.
A lemon squeezie type of cache with parking on site.

You might even be able to find it without getting
out of your car or off your bike, horse or whatever means of
transport you have at your disposal.

ul.li:
2010-06-04T19:00:00Z : Found it by Antefix
Of course we never heard of Surgalstown before... being Swiss [:D] Thanks for the cache.

2010-05-25T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by Serapis
This was frustrating – what I thought should be a quick find along the road was foiled by a car parked at the exact place. Cachers I thought, as there no reason why people would pull in here, the clearance off the road is not that good. But closer inspection revealed a old man asleep and his female partner reading the paper. What a place to stop. I went off for ‘a good walk’ and came back and they were still there. I’ll be back.

2010-05-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by st5346
Found this one on my way along the coast in a 2 week vacation in Ireland! Very nice place, thanks for sharing this one!

2010-03-15T19:00:00Z : Found it by Mausfallensteller
I never heard of Surgalstown too, my first cach in Ireland, and it's somewhere in the Nowhere! [;)]
in: TB 'save earth' out: TB Love bug pathag
TFTC
